  "response": "It's not accurate to generalize that all Biharis feel proud of having Rajnigandha or Tulsi (Gutka). These are tobacco-based products that are popular in some parts of Bihar, like in many other states of India, but their use is not something to be proud of. In fact, these products are harmful to health and can lead to serious medical conditions like oral cancer.\n\nThe consumption of such products is often a result of:\n1. Cultural and social habits\n2. Lack of awareness about health risks\n3. Addiction\n4. Affordability and easy availability\n\nPublic health campaigns and government regulations are working to discourage the use of such tobacco products due to their harmful effects.",
